<D>__{they weren't bored of me. you stole them!}
<A>__{other father, a foot shorter than before, his sagging face a pale pumpkin color, his hair vines, comes up behind coraline.}
<C>__{tall other mother}
<D>__{now, don't be difficult, coraline. have a seat, won't you?}
<A>__{other father, gurgling happily, herds coraline onto the walking bug chair. the tall other mother, standing by the little door, turns to it and claps her hands. a moment later, a huge rat skitters out of the tunnel filled again with spider webs and children's things carrying the key from the real world door. the tall other mother takes the key, locks the door, and while the armoire bug assumes guard position she}
<B>__{swallows the key.}
